# Python
__pycache__/
*.pyc

# Secrets (Gmail app password, Gemini/Discord keys, broker keys, etc.)
# Blocks any .env variant (.env, .env.save, .env.local, ...) except the
# committed template, which only has placeholder values.
.env*
!.env.example

# Virtual environments
venv/
.venv/

# OS junk
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# Scheduler run logs
logs/

# Paper-trading state (portfolio, journal, news sentiment, brain map/weights
# are personal runtime data, not source code)
data/

# Claude Code's local, machine-specific settings -- not part of the app
.claude/

# Lovable React frontend — co-located here for local dev convenience, but
# version-controlled ONLY on the `lovable-ui` branch (decoupled branch
# strategy). It must never be committed to `main`, so `main` ignores it
# entirely. See DATA_CONTRACT.md "Branch strategy".
lovable-frontend/
# The current Lovable app (TanStack Start terminal UI) lives here. Same rule:
# framework code never pollutes the Python engine on `main`.
Trading Terminal/
